  <original-body>Sometimes I need to reload some object from database, but I do not always need to reload every attribute. If I know what attribute I need to reload it would be great to do it, without performing huge select.

This patch is implementing this feature. It adds methods to AR::Base, equal to attribute names, but ending with exclamation mark. Such methods do reload attribute from database, but instead of:

select * from table_name;

it does

select field from table_name;

So, you can use @post.title, if you need to get a cached title, or you can use @post.title!, if you need to fetch it directly from database.</original-body>
